<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-03-07T22:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-03-07T22:00:00-05:00" n="618" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d618">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">818.6363 Am 6/68: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at San José</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-03-07T21:00:00-06:00"><hi rend="italic">March 7,
                                        1921—9 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received March 8(<hi rend="smallcaps">?</hi>)—11:47 a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>42. Congress this evening rejected Amory concession protocol by 24 to 10
                            votes. Will report promptly any consequences.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>